maplight
Sounds like he's talking about the Republican party which is why Trump resonated, whether he meant it, however crudely he went about it, however limited it might be he pushed back, wasn't afraid to push back, enjoyed pushing back. That defiance changed the debate within the Republican party, Cruz and Rubio caught on and switched from open borders to tough on immigration. Trump showed the absurdly preposterously named "religion of peace" a description invented by George W. Bush, could ne talked a out honestly without the sky falling. It was refreshing to see a Republican stand up for something after eight years.
